1449 <member name="T:Newtonsoft.Json.DefaultValueHandling">
1450 <summary>
1451 Specifies default value handling options for the <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonSerializer"/>.
1452 </summary>
1453 <example>
1454 <code lang="cs" source="..\Src\Newtonsoft.Json.Tests\Documentation\SerializationTests.cs" region="ReducingSerializedJsonSizeDefaultValueHandlingObject" title="DefaultValueHandling Class"/>
1455 <code lang="cs" source="..\Src\Newtonsoft.Json.Tests\Documentation\SerializationTests.cs" region="ReducingSerializedJsonSizeDefaultValueHandlingExample" title="DefaultValueHandling Ignore Example"/>
1456 </example>

1458 <member name="F:Newtonsoft.Json.DefaultValueHandling.Include">
1459 <summary>
1460 Include members where the member value is the same as the member's default value when serializing objects.
1461 Included members are written to JSON. Has no effect when deserializing.
1462 </summary>
1463 </member>
1464 <member name="F:Newtonsoft.Json.DefaultValueHandling.Ignore">
1465 <summary>
1466 Ignore members where the member value is the same as the member's default value when serializing objects
1467 so that is is not written to JSON.
1468 This option will ignore all default values (e.g. <c>null</c> for objects and nullable typesl; <c>0</c> for integers,
1469 decimals and floating point numbers; and <c>false</c> for booleans). The default value ignored can be changed by
1470 placing the <see cref="T:System.ComponentModel.DefaultValueAttribute"/> on the property.
1471 </summary>
1472 </member>
1473 <member name="F:Newtonsoft.Json.DefaultValueHandling.Populate">
1474 <summary>
1475 Members with a default value but no JSON will be set to their default value when deserializing.
1476 </summary>
1477 </member>
1478 <member name="F:Newtonsoft.Json.DefaultValueHandling.IgnoreAndPopulate">
1479 <summary>
1480 Ignore members where the member value is the same as the member's default value when serializing objects
1481 and sets members to their default value when deserializing.
1482 </summary>
1483 </member>

2090 <member name="P:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonConvert.DefaultSettings">
2091 <summary>
2092 Gets or sets a function that creates default <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonSerializerSettings"/>.
2093 Default settings are automatically used by serialization methods on <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonConvert"/>,
2094 and <see cref="M:Newtonsoft.Json.Linq.JToken.ToObject``1"/> and <see cref="M:Newtonsoft.Json.Linq.JToken.FromObject(System.Object)"/> on <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.Linq.JToken"/>.
2095 To serialize without using any default settings create a <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonSerializer"/> with
2096 <see cref="M:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonSerializer.Create"/>.
2097 </summary>

5092 <member name="M:Newtonsoft.Json.Linq.JValue.CompareTo(Newtonsoft.Json.Linq.JValue)">
5093 <summary>
5094 Compares the current instance with another object of the same type and returns an integer that indicates whether the current instance precedes, follows, or occurs in the same position in the sort order as the other object.
5095 </summary>
5096 <param name="obj">An object to compare with this instance.</param>
5097 <returns>
5098 A 32-bit signed integer that indicates the relative order of the objects being compared. The return value has these meanings:
5099 Value
5100 Meaning
5101 Less than zero
5102 This instance is less than <paramref name="obj"/>.
5103 Zero
5104 This instance is equal to <paramref name="obj"/>.
5105 Greater than zero
5106 This instance is greater than <paramref name="obj"/>.
5107 </returns>
5108 <exception cref="T:System.ArgumentException">
5109 <paramref name="obj"/> is not the same type as this instance.
5110 </exception>

5535 <member name="T:Newtonsoft.Json.MemberSerialization">
5536 <summary>
5537 Specifies the member serialization options for the <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonSerializer"/>.
5538 </summary>
5539 </member>
5540 <member name="F:Newtonsoft.Json.MemberSerialization.OptOut">
5541 <summary>
5542 All public members are serialized by default. Members can be excluded using <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonIgnoreAttribute"/> or <see cref="!:NonSerializedAttribute"/>.
5543 This is the default member serialization mode.
5544 </summary>
5545 </member>
5546 <member name="F:Newtonsoft.Json.MemberSerialization.OptIn">
5547 <summary>
5548 Only members must be marked with <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonPropertyAttribute"/> or <see cref="T:System.Runtime.Serialization.DataMemberAttribute"/> are serialized.
5549 This member serialization mode can also be set by marking the class with <see cref="T:System.Runtime.Serialization.DataContractAttribute"/>.
5550 </summary>
5551 </member>
5552 <member name="F:Newtonsoft.Json.MemberSerialization.Fields">
5553 <summary>
5554 All public and private fields are serialized. Members can be excluded using <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonIgnoreAttribute"/> or <see cref="!:NonSerializedAttribute"/>.
5555 This member serialization mode can also be set by marking the class with <see cref="!:SerializableAttribute"/>
5556 and setting IgnoreSerializableAttribute on <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.Serialization.DefaultContractResolver"/> to false.
5557 </summary>
5558 </member>

6244 <member name="M:Newtonsoft.Json.Serialization.DefaultContractResolver.#ctor(System.Boolean)">
6245 <summary>
6246 Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.Serialization.DefaultContractResolver"/> class.
6247 </summary>
6248 <param name="shareCache">
6249 If set to <c>true</c> the <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.Serialization.DefaultContractResolver"/> will use a cached shared with other resolvers of the same type.
6250 Sharing the cache will significantly performance because expensive reflection will only happen once but could cause unexpected
6251 behavior if different instances of the resolver are suppose to produce different results. When set to false it is highly
6252 recommended to reuse <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.Serialization.DefaultContractResolver"/> instances with the <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.JsonSerializer"/>.
6253 </param>

7125 <member name="P:Newtonsoft.Json.Serialization.MemoryTraceWriter.LevelFilter">
7126 <summary>
7127 Gets the <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.TraceLevel"/> that will be used to filter the trace messages passed to the writer.
7128 For example a filter level of <code>Info</code> will exclude <code>Verbose</code> messages and include <code>Info</code>,
7129 <code>Warning</code> and <code>Error</code> messages.
7130 </summary>
7131 <value>
7132 The <see cref="T:Newtonsoft.Json.TraceLevel"/> that will be used to filter the trace messages passed to the writer.
7133 </value>
7134 </member>
